hinese%20EVs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAutomakers%20are%20constantly%20learning%20from%20their%20competitors%20in%20China.%20Tesla%2C%20one%20of%20the%20leading%20EV%20companies%2C%20is%20no%20exception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-tesla-executive-fix-venture-capitals-addiction-to-fees-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJon%20McNeill%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20former%20president%20of%20Tesla's%20global%20sales%20and%20marketing%20who%20now%20sits%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeneral-motors-gm-layoffs-slower-ev-demand-regulatory-environment-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGeneral%20Motors'%20board%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Tesla%20has%20torn%20down%20Chinese%20EVs%20and%20that%20the%20lessons%20learned%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20some%20of%20Tesla's%20most%20popular%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTesla%20is%20a%20learning%20sponge%2C%26quot%3B%20McNeill%2C%20who%20was%20at%20the%20EV%20company%20between%202015%20and%202018%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20tenure%2C%20Model%203%20was%20in%20its%20infamous%20%26quot%3Bproduction%20hell%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20Tesla%20had%20just%20teased%20the%20first%20image%20of%20the%20Model%20Y.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20Tesla%20executive%20said%20one%20lesson%20learned%20from%20Chinese%20EVs%20was%20the%20reuse%20of%20parts%20%E2%80%94%20using%20some%20of%20the%20same%20guts%20of%20one%20model%20for%20another%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20can%20be%20seen%20%26quot%3Bacross%20the%203%20and%20the%20Y.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-ceo-elon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETesla%20CEO%20Elon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20a%202019%20earnings%20call%20that%20the%20Model%20Y%20shared%20about%20three-quarters%20of%20its%20parts%20with%20the%20Model%203%2C%20allowing%20for%20easier%20production%20ramp-up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Tesla%20did%20not%20return%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2237895e5c-58c2-46d6-86e5-7b48bf7faee2%5C%22%3EAnother%20level%20of%20reusing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMcNeill%20didn't%20name%20which%20Chinese%20EVs%20Tesla%20tore%20down%20during%20his%20tenure%2C%20but%20said%20he's%20recently%20seen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbyd-sales-competition-china-xpeng-nio-leapmotor-geely-tesla-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBYD%2C%20the%20leading%20EV%20maker%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20China%2C%20take%20the%20technique%20of%20reusing%20parts%20to%20another%20level%20at%20a%20teardown%20with%20GM.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Chinese%20engineers%20are%20really%20disciplined%20about%20reusing%20parts%20underneath%20the%20hood%20that%20the%20customer%20can't%20see%2C%20and%20they%20save%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20that%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20a%20unique%20concept%20to%20Chinese%20automakers%3B%20the%20automotive%20industry%20has%20long%20relied%20on%20using%20the%20same%20parts%20from%20one%20model%20of%20car%20for%20another%20in%20an%20automaker's%20lineup%2C%20including%20components%20such%20as%20the%20steering%20wheel%20or%20the%20turn-signal%20stalk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBYD%20and%20other%20Chinese%20automakers%2C%20however%2C%20are%20distinctive%20in%20the%20degree%20to%20which%20they%20reuse%20parts%20down%20to%20the%20ancillary%20components%20of%20a%20vehicle%2C%20from%20the%20battery%20packs%20to%20the%20heat%20pumps%20and%20motors%20inside%20the%20car%20seats%2C%20McNeill%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20tear%20down%20all%20the%20BYDs%20%E2%80%94%20same%20windshield%20wiper%20motor%20across%20all%20of%20them%3B%20same%20heat%20pump%20across%20all%20of%20them%3B%20same%20conduit%20across%20all%20of%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20other%20words%2C%20there's%20not%20a%20team%20that's%20designing%20a%20particular%20model%2C%20and%20they're%20off%20on%20their%20own.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcNeill%20added%20that%20the%20technique%20was%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20smart%20because%20a%20windshield%20wiper%20motor%20really%20doesn't%20change%20or%20add%20to%20the%20experience.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20practice%20is%20different%20from%20platform-sharing%2C%20in%20which%20the%20vehicle%20frame%20or%20the%20underlying%20architecture%20can%20be%20the%20same%20across%20models.%20Platform-sharing%20has%20become%20a%20central%20practice%20for%20EV%20automakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcNeill%20said%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20Chinese%20EV%20makers%20are%20reusing%20parts%20is%20not%20a%20common%20sight%20at%20other%20legacy%20automakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToyota%20uses%20completely%20different%20heat%20pumps%2C%20wiper%20motors%2C%20and%20seat%20actuators%20for%20each%20model.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20guts%20of%20a%20Corolla%20is%20almost%20completely%20different%20from%20a%20Camry%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpokespeople%20for%20BYD%20and%20Toyota%20did%20not%20return%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22549f1642-1997-4a5e-8cef-7e586c821b4e%5C%22%3ENew%20automakers%20need%20to%20cut%20costs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EReusing%20parts%20is%20crucial%20for%20any%20automaker%20to%20scale%20production%20efficiently%20and%20reduce%20costs.%20That%20could%20be%20even%20more%20true%20for%20emerging%20automakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20reason%20only%20one%20auto%20company%20has%20been%20started%20and%20scaled%20in%20the%20last%20hundred%20years%2C%20and%20it's%20because%20it's%20really%20hard.%20It's%20really%2C%20really%20hard%20and%20it's%20really%20capital-intensive%2C%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMcNeill%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20Tesla.%20He%20added%20that%20a%20US%20EV%20company%20like%20Tesla%20needs%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Babsolutely%20relentless%26quot%3B%20at%20reducing%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22R